x4freetext: Experiment performed using Coupled
Cyclotron Facility and fragment separator at National
Superconducting Cyclotron Laboratory at MSU
Metallic foil with thickness of
9.62 mg/cm2
Sample was placed at the pivot point of the
S800 spectrograph set for a central scattering angle
of 0deg. The 3He2+ ejectiles from the (t,3He)
reactions were momentum-analyzed in the S800 focal
plane.
A plastic scintillator was placed in the S800
focal plane to measure particle energy los
Energy measurement was made using time of
flight relative to cyclotron radiofrequency signal,
dE was measured using plastic scintillator.
A primary beam of 16-O-8+ ions at 150 AMeV produced
at the National Superconducting Cyclotron Laboratory
Coupled Cyclotron Facility was impinged upon a 3526
mg/cm2 thick beryllium target to produce a 115-AMeV
secondary triton beam. An isotopic purity of better
than 99% was obtained in the A1900 fragment
separator. An average triton beam intensity of 7E+6
particles/s was achieved
